Sigma 30 f/1.4: Jazz camp in awful, awful light
Every year TC has an improv jazz camp for middle and high school students. I knew it would be the perfect test for this lens because it takes place in a very dark chapel where the tiny lighting is directly overhead and very unflattering. Last year's camp was the only event I've shot as part of my job where I considered the results simply unusable. Here's what the Sigma did with it.
